# ── Zig Build ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The incremental compilation cache is ephemeral and environment-specific.
# Storing it would bloat the repo and cause conflicts between developer setups.
.zig-cache/

# Binaries and libraries produced by the build process. These are the final
# output and should be reproducible from source, not tracked in version control.
zig-out/

# Dependency cache managed by Zig's package manager. Keeping this out of git
# ensures that dependencies are always fetched and verified against their hashes.
zig-pkg/

# ── Generated Data & Binary Artifacts ────────────────────────────────
# Binary dataset files (mmap'd indices and lookup tables). These are large,
# non-diffable, and machine-specific. They must be regenerated via the
# data-prep pipeline to ensure integrity.
data/*.bin
resources/*.bin

# ── Benchmark Artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Performance metrics and execution results. These are snapshots in time
# and vary by hardware; they should be analyzed in isolation, not committed.
results.json
tests/benchmark/results.json

# ── Native Compiler Artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────
# Low-level object files and library archives from C/Fortran FFI.
# These are transient intermediates of the compilation process.
*.mod
*.o
*.obj
*.out
*.a
*.so
*.dylib

# ── Editor / IDE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Personal productivity tools and IDE state. These preferences belong to
# the individual developer, not the project's shared configuration.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.dir-locals.el

# ── OS Metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Filesystem noise generated by desktop environments. These add no value
# to the project and can vary significantly across platforms.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ── Temporary Files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Log files and temporary buffers. These are short-lived and should never
# persist beyond their immediate use case.
*.log
*.tmp

# ── Local Data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
resources/references.json
